2022-02-15 07:47,2022-02-15 07:47,"Diary",,,,"the right way for a toddler to experience sadness","I cry semi-regularly in front of my children and it's normally because of them. Big triggers for me are dying and missing out on experiences with you or regretting things I did wrong. Movies will of course get me going, but I particularly enjoy a good emotional book. I picked one in particular ""scar"", it starts with a punch I think the first line is ""My mother died yesterday"". The book is about the child's process of navigating death and really focuses on the responsibilities felt by that child. I think I started crying the first page :). Theo didn't really react much differently than any other book. Both kids were engaged while I read it. Charlie got a in her own head, her movements and reactions became slower like she was processing something. I looked at her and explained I expect to be with you for a very long time as long as you need me and often when you don't. This sadness seemed to track with her for a few minutes, but then went away. This isn't a new reaction from Charlie she will often separate herself when experiencing sadness, this most often happens when she did something wrong. It's like she's really considering the situation. I also gave my general ""feeling all the feels is important: speech.  Justine thought, and I kind of agree, that this book could do some damage early on so even though Charlie intentionally picked it out several times I started to nerf the content a lot.","Jim","Charlie"

2022-02-13 10:25,2022-02-13 10:25,"Diary",,,,"Viewpoint change","I used to view kids as more of an obligation and not as much fun there's probably a lot of reasons for that but it affected my understanding of how other people would interact with them.   Like I tried to push Gigi out when she was done watching them after a full day because I assume she didn't want to be around them anymore because a larger part of me didn't want to be around them.  Now that I enjoy the majority of time I spend with you both I don't feel as bad about impromptu visits to Gigi's house or I don't take it as a personal insult when GG stays around after I get done with work I understand because I can empathize that I want to spend time with you.","Jim","Charlie"

And Charlie said ""No, I want paste!"" she said the same thing about going to Costco over swimming.","Jim","Charlie"

She was just pressing down on the soap chunks through the water grate.  	she later got sad that she wasn't able to get a solid piece down, so I gave her a few tips like press down with you palm and she started doing better. 2022-02-12 07:30,2022-02-12 07:30,"Diary",,,,"Charlie is so damn considerate of people feelings: reassred me it was ok Theo pooped in the bath","	We had just got finished with the really cool bath time toy improv and Theo just started pooping. I notice it, but was confused for a second that it's actually happening. Like I had thought earlier today that I was surprised this hasn't happened in like 4-5 months, I had thought I was done with this happening, lol. But I rush Charlie out of the bath and she's nervous/sad because she suddenly went from bath time fun to out of bath without warning. I get out with Theo and put him in the shower, which he is loving cause he loves to squeegee the windows. Charlie's asks to poop on the potty, I think because she was nervous about me being irritated that kids were pooping where they shouldn't maybe, which is another sad sign about how much I show my irritation. This starts making more sense when I hear Charlie say multiple times ""it happens"", When she says this Charlie is looking up at me for confirmation that I understand pooping in the bath isn't a big deal. She does this several times with her arms held above her shoulders palms up shrugging. Which is cute that she knows the universal gesture for that saying. This was so disarming that I really took note of it as Charlie very often takes my and other's feelings into consideration. She has the visibility into peoples emotional state and has the concern and comfort needed to start calming a situation. I don't know how normal this is at such a young age, but I love it.","Jim","Charlie"
2022-02-12 07:26,2022-02-12 07:26,"Diary",,,,"differences: playing make believe (charlie is much more advanced in playing make believe)","During Bathtime we imrpovised make believe characters playing out a dynamic where the daddy brochiasorus(dad-brock) is the only dinosaur bath toy that can float and Theo was holding it. I tried to engage Theo in make believe by asking his daddy-brock to ferry across the trex-baby. I kept explaining that in several different ways, but Theo didn't pick up on it until I started being more direct like ""Theo take your big dinosaur and come over to the trex-baby so it can help move it from this side of the tub to the other"" and Theo started to interact. Charlie really wanted to play with us at this point so I gave her the babby-brok, she went up to Theo and tried to get the message across that it was Theos toy's baby, but Theo didn't get this. To appease Charlie who was starting to get frustrated at Theo not understanding. I took out the daddy trex and the baby one theo had previously helped ferry across the bath and started having them interact so Charlie and I just started playing a separate game where those two interacted. Charlie then tried to bring Theo into the game with us by using her baby-brok to call over his daddy-brok. After the both of us trying to explain what we were doing to Theo a couple times he started understanding and using his daddy-brok to interact with the baby-brok in a way that makes sense like saying high and it's ok to it. I then used daddy-trex to talk with Theo's daddy-brok I said  		J: ""we found your lost kid... we're glad you're ok"".  		T: ""ok ... ok ...""  	Although, after bath Theo and I made believe we're trying to hide from something --> Theo was very good at pretending and improv. So seems like he plays in a more tactile/emotional thinker than his sister who like to have character interactions and games","Jim","Charlie"

2022-02-7 10:26,2022-02-7 10:26,"Diary",,,,"So independent!","Today while we were playing in the basement Charlie noticed she had a hole in her pajama pants. She walked over to the door and said be right back… Two minutes… Need new pants… Be back two minutes.  I knew she was going up to her bedroom to get some new pants to put on. So I pulled her up on her camera. She could not turn on the bedroom light to see the pants in the drawer. She walked over to the closet and turned on the light switch but didn’t open the door. Then she said can’t do it… She looked around and went over to her little mirror and stool. She grabbed the stool put it underneath the ceiling fan and stepped up on it. Looked up at the ceiling fan string that turns on the light and said can’t reach. Then she got down the stool and said need help. She started to walk out of the bedroom door and I turn on the microphone to talk to her. I called her back Jan and told her to open her closet door and turn the light so she can see her pants. I asked her if she could hear me to say hello. She said hello! Then she saw pink heart overalls in the closet and wanted to wear those but could not get them down. She came out of the closet and said need help! Looking at the camera. I told her Theo and Charlie were on our way up to help her.","Karen","Charlie"
2022-02-6 20:46,2022-02-6 20:46,"Diary",,,,"Can be reasoned with and considerate","I didn't have a pink sippy cup for milk clean and I poured to Blue sippy cups Charlie at first asked for her pink regular cup we couldn't find it and then ask for a pink sippy cup and I was able to reason with her by saying I don't have any that are clean sorry I know you really want the pink sippy cup and I understand it's important to you but can you take the blue one this time please and she didn't without major objection.  I've got a pretty bad headache and light sensitivity right now and Charlie was amenable on several points will put it down she was in a playful mood and I asked her too lie down cuz Daddy's having a tough time so I can put down your diaper and she did she wanted a third book and I said honey daddy's really tired can we start the song and she left the closet. She proceeded to ask too be chased but wasn't too upset when I didn't. We're nearly had a breakdown when her normal small blue cup wasn't available for her bed and she didn't want the bigger bottle but I again was able to talk her off that ledge.","Jim","Charlie"

2022-02-6 09:09,2022-02-6 09:09,"Diary",,,,"Potty trained amazing","We went out to the library and then to Costco Charlie held in her pee the entire time.  There was a little meltdown in the cafeteria of Costco where Charlie wanted to hold the ice cream and I didn't want her to hold it until it wasn't overflowing. So she cried under the table for 5 minutes until she probably got up and said pee pee.  Lady across from us said she would watch her stuff and I ran with everything that couldn't be replaced to the bathroom. Holding both kids brought them into a single stall as all the stalls were taken. I took off Charlie's shirt then her tutu then her pants then her underwear and she sat down the toilet like it was nothing went pee and was great she did start looking under the stall walls at the other people pooping I assume which I had to discourage.  Got back to the table everything was still there and I was able to coax Charlie out of under the table crying again to feed her a couple of bites of the ice cream then let her have it as it was less messy at that point and she's really good eating ice cream.  As I talk to text this story Charlie I said shopping? And then crying? And I asked her why she was crying she said no have ice cream play reiterated that we had to share it and she seemed to agree love you","Jim","Charlie"

2022-01-26 19:37,2022-01-26 19:37,"Diary",,,,"The adult relationship they want to act out the most","I brought new toys into the bath today they're the little puppy toys that we bought to fit in the dollhouse there's about 10 of them.  Both kids immediately start playing with them and I use them as a lawyer to get them up in the bath. After a couple of minutes of playing Charlie organically by herself brought up where mama where mama. The next 20 minutes of bath was spent with a puppy trying to find their adult.  For Charlie that I told was mama and continue to be Mama for the entire time. Theo started emulating Charlie and saying mama but then switch to where Gigi where Gigi.","Jim","Charlie"

2022-01-26 19:10,2022-01-26 19:10,"Diary",,,,"I feel bad being the bad guy when they try to protect their baby dolls","When I play Daddy robot or daddy monster and Chase the kids around they'll often hide in the castle. I'll pretend to have taking one of the kids and the other kid will definitely come out and say that captured child.  It feels very evil when the kids are saying no no baby and they run out to protect their baby from the evil robot. Just seems like another level of bad guy that I feel uncomfortable at.","Jim","Charlie"

Charlie answered no and then paused for a couple seconds said boo boo pointing to her leg with intonation that she was correcting me","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-26 11:49,2022-01-26 11:49,"Diary",,,,"Got covid tested today.","Justine showed symptoms of omicron yesterday and rapid tested negative. 2022-01-25 20:07,2022-01-25 20:07,"Diary",,,,"Really wanted to wear puppy shirt","Charlie's been wearing this puppy shirt for 2 days and I went to put her clothes on before bed I made the mistake of asking do you want to wear the Kitty shirt. There's another shirt that looks more like puppies but was still a fox and she again said no Fox.  She wasn't happy about it but I got her into a My Little pony shirt mom brought her a puppy toy and she held that as compensation","Jim","Charlie"

It was a lot of fun Charlie got in and started playing with toys like normal but soon transition to swimming after toys that floated away. Charlie even made a floating ship out of the letter floaties and put some duck toys on top of it","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-19 22:30,2022-01-19 22:30,"Diary",,,,"Saying I love you regularly","Charlie will often say to Theo before going to bed.  Theo started to say it to whoever puts him to bed.","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-18 07:38,2022-01-18 07:38,"Diary",,,,"My life revolves around you, but your mom will always be my number one",,"Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-17 12:22,2022-01-17 12:22,"Diary",,,,"Telling time","I try to be as accurate as possible when I give time frames for when something's going to happen to the minute I think doing so helps them understand time and build credibility","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-17 10:00,2022-01-17 10:00,"Diary",,,,"Charlie starting to emerge as the leader","Charlie takes the initiative normally in small things like starting play with different games or engaging Theo when he's sad. But Theo starting to take more subtle cues from her too.  As I open the door to the garage to load them in the car to go to the museum with Papa and Granny. Charlie started inching back. She has some hesitancy towards the cold, but I think this is mostly becoming game. Theo noticed her moving backwards and started to move backwards with her. This is of no because I've usually been able to coax Theo into the garage, but not this time.   They both inch backwards for probably 15 ft until they turned and ran in both hid in the castle they were there for probably 30 seconds just calmly talking to each other before I came in and got them","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-17 09:59,2022-01-17 09:59,"Diary",,,,"Refuse a call to adventure","I was putting on Charlie's shoes as she was totally engrossed in this bubble popping toy and I said in my best Bilbo baggins voice we're going on an adventure.   Charlie then said with no pause very calmly no.","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-17 08:28,2022-01-17 08:28,"Diary",,,,"Twin communication really getting good","I was upstairs with Charlie and Theo was calling for Mommy. Charlie heard this and went back into the master bedroom to double check that there was no mommy there and she knew she left 15 minutes before. Charlie came out and said to feel no Mommy here.  Try single little hesitant to come downstairs until I said he was crying he needs us and then she started walking down the stairs saying help help. As in she was going to help Theo.  We got downstairs and Charlie was explaining to Theo mommy gone daddy day. As a matter of fact","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-16 20:25,2022-01-16 20:25,"Diary",,,,"Fathering High","Just 4mg of THC and I have a completely different experiences with you both. I'm more interested and perceptive. I'm more creative and playful. That perceptiveness is two-sided as I get nervous easily like Charlie introducing a new behavior of saying ""tummy hurts"" when she means to say I'm hungry. So now it's hard to distinguish when she's sick and needs help or just needs some food. So when she starts saying tummy hurts starting at 7pm and eats a piece and a half of jam toast and goes down with mommy to eat more, and even with all that continues saying tummy hurts I'm more likely to think we should call an urgent care rather than maybe she just was hungry ate too much and then her stomach is painfully distended.   But on the positive side I am able to create a pseudo imaginary friend situation out of us all interacting with the moon and becoming friends and then putting to bed.   I read a robot destroys the town comic style book with Charlie and added the sound effects and cinematic voices in. I linger longer on the pages of a book, asking/answering questions, or pointing out details I notice and suggesting she do the same.    ","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-16 16:57,2022-01-16 16:57,"Diary",,,,"Feelings about being a dad right now","I think I'm a good dad but I have a lot of personality traits that make it harder than it should be. It's definitely the most difficult thing I've done in my life by a wide margin","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-16 07:49,2022-01-16 07:49,"Diary",,,,"Morning conversation with Charlie","Good morning how was your sleep Good Mommy and Daddy went to bed too late mommy was working on the trip in the bathroom See it, Charlie says eagerly getting up and walking herself downstairs","Jim","Charlie"
2022-01-13 18:17,2022-01-13 18:17,"Diary",,,,"Understood a joke for the first time","Charlie talked about how Penny's tummy is sick I said I don't think she's sick why do you think she's sick.  Charlie said no sick. I asked what makes Penny sick and Charlie answered with grapes  A fake velcro grape toy was on the ground and I said oh no grapes in a fake concerned voice. Charlie initially looked concerned and then upon seeing the fake grapes started to laugh","Jim","Charlie"

Theo consoled Charlie after she realized she couldn't get into the staged ice cream truck. Charlie laid down in this foot step of the vehicle and felt sad for a bit, and Theo kept saying ""Sorry Charlie"" and rubbing her back until she got up 30 seconds later.   We looked at the fox exhibit where I pointed out bird wings on the ground from a meal they had earlier and Charlie felt pretty bad about that saying ""no, no no don't eat."" to the stuffed foxes.   Charlie played with he shadow in a darkened room with projected ceiling lights resembling water.   We spent 10 minutes at the marshland exhibit pressing the bird and frog sound buttons and pointing out different animals we saw.   At the treehouse are Theo gathered all of the puppets and put on a little one man show. While Charlie climbed the steep stairs with a book and asked for ""Theo come house read book"" a couple times, but he was pretend sleeping with the puppets under the treehouse.   All 3 of us eliminated waste at the bathroom where I put on llama llama for a couple minutes to do some toddler crowd control. I left my jacket in trying to manage everyone and no one complained as we dodged the ticket line and road the elevator back up and down to get it.   Theo was very into the drawers containing bugs and such and pulled them all out and used a magnifying glass (probably not well) to view some of the items. He pushed all the drawers in when he was done.   We had apple sauce and cheerios on the ride home and everyone braved the cold and had patience in the car so well. I just felt like we were all communicating and enjoying each others company.   You both went down for naps, but I had to come back upstairs after mom put you down Charlie b/c you wanted me to sing you to sleep. I'm thinking of learning the lyrics of a song a work day so I can have a nice little repertoire to sing to you as I am really struggling to remember songs in the moment as I put you to bed. You've heard rodeo like 30 times by now. Theo woke up in just the perfect mood. He cried for like 2 seconds, but was clingy for a couple minutes until he just became excited and wanted to play.  We went to the library, then Costco. It was a little colder as the sun was setting, but you both handled the cold on your faces and hands for the 50 yards to the door very well. We ate Costco pizza for dinner. We turned the music up and rolled the back window down as you yelled high and waved at all the people walking by. I had so much fun in that car just watching you both enjoying life.  We agreed that we would finish the Encanto movie and eat popcorn when we got home. ","Jim","Charlie"

2021-05-19 09:27,2021-05-19 09:27,"Diary",,,,"Very pleasant morning with twins","Theo woke me up a tiny bit early from an intricate heist dream at 6:24, but both kids were playing in bed until I came to get them. I think the light helped with their adjustment rather than turning on the main light right away. Theo made the sign for water and drank a couple ounces right away.  I setup the hatch sound machine to change sound to ""birds chirping"" and a green light at 7:30. So this was the first morning the kids woke up to that. I paused for 10 seconds before walking in. Both kids we very curious, with Theo being a little cautious about it.   We came downstairs in sleepers, neither had peed that much during the night. Charlie asked to turn the sound machine off. Both kids brought their lovies downstairs with them. I had steamed carrots ready and Charlie ate a couple while taking the lid on and off. She chased brother a couple steps as he ran away from her trying to feed him carrots. A little bit later Charlie changed tactics and placed a carrot on that table in front of him and Theo ate it before spitting most of it out a minute later.  We played with babies in strollers, cars and toys for 15 minutes. Charlie and Theo both drank a green tea I poured into their small cups. Charlie posed for a photo with me. She was smiling and we both held up our cups. She's saying cheese now in response to getting photos taken.  For breakfast Theo ate everything on his plate (eggs, fiber one cereal bits, mandarin orange, carrot) and got some of sisters oranges and eggs. Charlie has gotten in the habit of drinking a decent amount of dads veggie smoothie (spinach, celery, keifer, skyr, blue berries, inulin powder). I give her frozen chunks initially and sometimes I'll give her the cup when there's only a little left and she'll drink it straight. Charlie also ate a lot of food all together and both kids are in a often hungry phase which is to contrast a couple weeks ago when they were in a never hungry phase. ","Jim","Charlie"
